Role: Senior Data Scientist (ML Virtual Assistant Builder)

Employer: Bell (Contract Role through Eagle Professional Services)

Overview
Contributed to Bell’s Virtual Assistant program, leading the enhancement of multiple chatbot solutions. Delivered both employee-facing and customer-facing assistants, ensuring scalability and improved user experience across Bell’s major mobility brands.

Key Responsibilities

Developed and refined four chatbot solutions: one internal (employee-facing) assistant and three external-facing assistants for Bell Mobility, Lucky Mobile, and Virgin Mobile.

Designed and optimized conversational flows for both voice and text interactions.

Integrated advanced features and connected chatbots with multiple internal and external systems via APIs.

Applied machine learning, natural language understanding, and dialogue management techniques to improve intelligence and usability.

Supported prototyping, user testing, documentation, and stakeholder presentations.

Skills & Expertise

Conversational AI and enterprise-scale virtual assistant development.

Strong knowledge of machine learning, deep learning, and NLP concepts.

Hands-on experience building scalable AI-driven chatbots for large customer bases across multiple brands.

Collaboration and communication in enterprise environments, with experience presenting technical outcomes to business stakeholders.

Impact

Independently owned modules while contributing to broader team initiatives.

Enhanced customer and employee experiences through intelligent assistants, advancing Bell’s AI-driven transformation in telecommunications and mobility services.
